64.name: Heavy Mettle
64.description: Government funded super-team briefly led by Supreme.

65.name: Team 1
65.description: Team 1 was a team made of some of the characters that would go on to be members of Stormwatch and Wild C.A.T.S. The team was created by Lord Emp to combat the emerging Daemonite threat.

66.name: Coalition of Planets
66.description: The Coalition of Planets is an alliance between several alien races in the Invincible universe. The Coalition was formed to find a way to stop the Viltrumites.

67.name: Elephantmen
67.description: The Elephantmen are a group of Human/Animal hybrids created by the MAPPO corporation.

68.name: Unholy Alliance
68.description: A group of villains led by Demolitia. In 1998, they attacked Detroit as part of the conquistador's grand scheme to discredit america's hero.

69.name: Wildcore
69.description: A group of Kherubim and super-powered humans assembled by PSI to fight the forces of the D'rahn. Team leader Backlash and Co Leader's Taboo and Zealot(to Backlash chagrin)

70.name: Cyber Force
70.description: Cyber Force is a Top Cow Superhero team created by artist Marc Silvestri and writer Eric Silvestri in 1992.The idea of the book is that a group of mutants that were capture by Cyberdata and were experimented on to become S.H.O.C.s(Special Hazardous Operations Cyborg) but soon after they broke out and from Cyber Force to fight Cyberdata.

71.name: Freedom Phalanx
71.description: Officially founded on July 4, 1932, The Freedom Phalanx was the first ever registered superhero group in Paragon City. After two decades that bore witness to World War I and The Great Depression, The Freedom Phalanx would become a beacon of light for heroism & justice.

72.name: Arachnos
72.description: Originally a former Italian Facist group, it quietly grew over decades under the command of the technocrat and mastermind, Lord Recluse.

73.name: Hunter-Killer
73.description: Forget what they teach you in History class.  World War I? II? Cuban Missile Crisis? Cold War?  All of these events revolved around the trading and stockpiling of superhumans, or Ultra Sapiens.  Now underground, they are pursued by the Hunter Killer teams.

74.name: The Fraternity
74.description: The Fraternity is the group of super villains that rule the world of Wanted. They consist of 5 separate families, ruling different parts of the world. The main protagonists in Wanted are members of the North American family.

75.name: Council of Five
75.description: The Council of Five is the group of supervillains that control the world.

76.name: Strykeforce
76.description: A mercenary team led by Morgan Stryker of CyberForce. The team travels the globe performing missions including protection, retrieval, and intervention, for the right price.
76.appear: The Tin Men of War: Part Four

78.name: Freshmen
78.description: They are college kids who were granted odd powers when the ax-cell-erator exploding giving them powers based on their actions at the given moment.

79.name: Aggressive Solutions International
79.description: A.S.I. is the corporate face of a criminal syndicate. They possess vast resources and  have highly trained mega-tech empowered individuals at their disposal. Their primary work comes from secretly contracting out their special (and illegal) services to high paying clients.

80.name: Psi Lords
80.description: Psi Lords are aliens who are watching the earth in the Valiant Universe.

82.name: H.A.R.D. Corps
82.description: H.A.R.D. Corps (Harbinger Active Resistance Division) is a team of humans with brain implants that give them the ability to download super powers. They hunt down super powered psiots (Harbingers) in the Valiant Universe. Capture or death by enemies causes their brain implants to explode.

83.name: Secret Weapons
83.description: Secret Weapons is a Team in the Valiant Universe.

84.name: The Force
84.description: The Force is a team in the Valiant Universe. They appear in Eternal Warrior.

85.name: Star Soldiers
85.description:
Star Soldiers are Characters in the Valiant Universe. 
They have space armors to guard Toyo Harada's holdings.

86.name: Futureforce
86.description: The Futureforce are freedom fighters for mankind who fight in the against the Malev Emperor and his robot empire in the 41st century.

87.name: Young Wolves
87.description:
Young Wolves is a team in the Valiant Universe: 
Spikey and Pert, Sam the Neo Dog, and the Outsiders teamed up and named themselfes "Young Wolves".

88.name: Quantum & Woody
88.appear: Quantum and Woody: The Director's Cut

89.name: Freewill Robots
89.description: Freewill Robots are "living" in the Valiant Universe. The first freewill was 1-A who raised Magnus Robot Fighter.

90.name: The Losers
90.description: Ex-CIA team who seek revenge against their handler Max after he betrayed them.

91.name: Minutemen
91.description: The enformers of the Trust who were responsible for policing all thirteen families. Their role was to maintain the status quo. Acting as judge, jury and executioner, they settled disputes in blood.
91.appear: The Right Ear, Left in the Cold, Part Two

92.name: The Endless
92.description: The Endless are seven siblings that embody seven different fundamental forces of existence itself. Ageless, immortal and nigh-omnipotent, these siblings were the central characters of the landmark Vertigo series "The Sandman".

93.name: Yahweh's Children
93.description: Yahweh's Children is not the official name of any team, though it is the union of Michael, Lucifer and Elaine, his true descendants.
93.appear: The Wolf Beneath the Tree: Part 3 of 4

94.name: The Grail
94.description: A secret organization dedicated to keeping the bloodline of Jesus Christ intact.

95.name: Les Enfents du Sang
95.description: A group of wannabe vampires in New Orleans.

96.name: Honor Guard
96.description: Astro City's most famous and most powerful group of heroes. It was founded in 1959 by the size-changing Max O'Millions.

97.name: The Trust
97.description: A secret society composed of thirteen families which can only be described as "very old, very powerful and very dirty" It's origins go back to the late 15th Century.

98.name: Recipients of the Attaché
98.description: These are the individuals have received one of Agent Graves Attachés complete with information about the person who ruined their lives, a gun, 100 bullets and the immunity to do justice themselves. While some succeeded in this task, others failed...failure equaling death.

99.name: Adephi
99.appear: And The Horse You Rode In On

60.name: Youngblood
60.description: Youngblood is a team of superheroes hired by the United States government.

61.name: Brigade
61.description: A rogue mercenary team lead by Battlestone. Brigade has fought against corrupt government agencies.

62.name: The Atomics
62.description: A Super Hero team that consists of Madman and his most trusted friends.

63.name: Vicious Circle
63.description: A team of evil super-freaks who operate out of Chicago, they have come at odds with Savage Dragon, Superpatriot, Star, and Freak Force. The group was led by Overlord.
